inn1.comm: loud shout for lbw. That was close.  It landed back of length, on the leg and middle and hit him high in front of middle. The height must have saved him there.
walks out and drives straight to short cover
shuffles across, gets the ball from around off and middle and flicks it for a single
around the off stump, bit of inswing, Aaron Redmond pushes it out to the off side.
around the off stump, shaping away this time, Redmond leans across to defend to the off side
cracking square drive. Fullish, pushed across Redmond who plays it past the diving point fielder
lovely delivery, moving away late and McCullum is beaten, pushing inside the line
lands on a length outside off and goes to the keeper
full in length, straightening on the middle stump line. pushed back to the bowler
walks across to the off side and shoulders arms
his back foot is in line with the middle stump and he places the bat down on the ground outside the off stump. He gets behind the line of this length delivery to defend
around the off stump, pushed to extra cover for a single
moves forward and jabs it out to the off side
walks down the track and a has a big slog across the line but can't get bat on ball...
shuffles across to clip a back-of-length delivery to deep square-leg region
shout for lbw but turned down. Again, McCullum was on the shuffle and is hit in front of leg and middle. But it pitched outside leg stump
bangs it in short, McCullum drops his wrists, gets the bat out of the way and sways away
on the middle stump line, worked towards deep backward square-leg and runs hard to come back for the second
on the middle stump line, pushed towards mid-on and he scampers across and dives in the end to get inside the crease
Shot. It was the bouncer and McCullum plays a lovely crunchy pull shot. Perhaps. Gul thought McCullum would be advancing down the track
back of length, outside the off stump, McCullum gets the bottom edge on the cut shot
just outside off stump, defended to cover
leans forward to defend a length delivery
back of length, on the middle, tapped close on the leg side and off they go for the quick single

Full in length, moving across Redmond who tries to lift it over the off-side field but mistimes it straight to mid-off.  The bat-face wobbled at the point of impact and he couldn't time or provide any power to that shot.
moving away from the batsman who pushes inside the line and Kamran collects
fullish, on the middle, trying to get the lbw but Guptill is alert, makes sure the front leg doesn't come in the way and whips the ball through midwicket
lands on a length around off and moves away further, left alone
lands just outside off and angles away, left alone
full in length, around off stump, runs off the inner half of the bat to mid-on
length delivery, moves into the off stump line, defended back down the track
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
fullish, on the middle and leg, whipped straight to midwicket.
beaten by the slower one. Gul floated it full well outside off and McCullum went after it but fails to connect

another slower one but this time McCullum gets it through the gap. It was full and outside off, McCullum didn't seem in control of the straight drive but managed to get it in the gap between the bowler and mid-off
Top shot. Not all that short, not all that far away from the off stump but he stayed adjacent to the line and forced it through point.
lands on the middle and off, moves towards off, pushed out to cover
drops it short and Guptill pulls it over midwicket. That was well put away; he got into a superb position
moves outside leg stump but Aamer pushes it wide outside off. Free hit remains
opened up his stance and swung the length delivery across the line but couldn't time it well and hit it straight to mid-on
slower one, full around the off and middle line, leans forward to defend
angles it across Guptill who lets it go through to Kamran
leans across to push past extra cover for a single
stays back to work the back-of-length delivery to midwicket for a single
takes a couple of steps down the track, Gul shortens the length and McCullum defends
short in length, cuts in to clip the back pad, outside the off stump, and rolls through to the keeper
gets behind the line of a short-of-length delivery and taps it close towards midwicket and rushes across for a risky single. Yousuf is slow in getting to the ball and McCullum gets across in time
around the off stump line, guided to backward point
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
shuffles across and tries to flick a full delivery from around the off stump through midwicket, misses and it rolls off the pad ...
angles it across Guptill who lets it go past the off stump

shout for a catch behind but turned down. It was the full delivery slanted across Guptill who went for a drive. The ball went low to right of Kamran who lunged to take it. There was some noise but no visual evidence on the replay
goes right back to punch a short-of-length delivery through midwicket. Very well timed and they will get back for the third run
on the leg stump line, tapped to the on side for a run. Another Free hit coming up.
The lemon cut is out! He cleared the front leg and went for a big swing over midwicket but edges it past the short fine-leg fielder.
slower one well outside the off stump, McCullum goes for the big drive but misses it.The ball swung away and McCullum hit the ground. Strange, it hasn't been called a wide.
pushes through to the off side for a single
on the off stump line, pushed to backward point
just outside the off stump, tries to run it down to third man but doesn't connect
outside off stump, left alone
pushes this one through point and will pick up two runs
banged in short, pulled away over midwicket
leans forward to push to the off side
full in length, in the zone outside off, left alone
slightly slower, on the off stump line, punched past Ajmal at mid-on. Ajmal should have stopped that but his dive was very awkward. Geoff Boycott on air calls it as, "Awful belly flop!"
on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
It's Ajmal again. They push it towards him at mid-on and rush for the single
length delivery on the off and middle line, stabbed off the inner edge

almost done in by the slower one. Gul has slipped in quite a few slower ones today. This was around the off stump, and McCullum checked his drive, got the bottom-hand off the handle and pushed at it. The ball falls just short of Afrid at short cover
overpitches on this occasion and on the middle and leg line as well, McCullum whips it to deep midwicket boundary
back of length, around the off stump, tapped to the off side
leans across to push to left of cover and Afridi fires in a direct hit at the striker's end
whiplashed away. It was full and well outside off, Guptill threw the sink at it and the ball flew past point
leans forward to defend.
Whack! It was banged in short and McCullum swiveled superbly off the front foot and pulled it high over backward square-leg boundary
leans forward to push it to the off side
Wallop! Top shot. It was slightly short in length outside off and McCullum lashes it past point with a fierce cut. Again, it wasn't all that short, nor was it far from the off stump.
leans forward to push it to mid-on

full in length, leans across to push to right of backward point .. Malik lunges out to make a half-stop and fires in a throw at the non-striker's end but misses and they take the extra run on the overthrow
quickish delivery on the off and middle, pushed to the on side of the pitch and Ajmal makes a lunging stop
slows up the pace, flighted around off and middle, defended back down the track
skips down the track and on drives to long-on
on the middle and leg, pushed to the on side
quicker one, on the middle and leg, defended to midwicket
on the off stump line, again quick, defended to the off side
leans forward to defend a length delivery
pushed out towards mid-off and they get across for the single. Baz on strike
Thwack. He fetches the length delivery from almost outside off stump and thrashes it past midwicket!
leans forward to push to cover point
short in length, around off stump line, pulled away to Latif at deep square-leg region. Latif hurls in a wide throw to backward point! Kamran is not amused and Latif puts his hand up in apology
tip and run. They run with the defensive push.  The two have been really testing out the Pakistan fielders.
moves down the track and pushes it to midwicket
on the middle and off, driven back to the bowler
slower through the air, goes right back and across to tuck it behind square-leg
flighted outside off, leans across to squeeze it to backward point
on the middle stump line, driven down to long-on
shout for lbw but it struck him outside off. It was a flighted delivery, McCullum stumbled forward, failed to connect with his defensive poke and was hit on the pad outside off
on the middle and off line, flicked to left of short midwicket where Yousuf fields and fires in a direct hit at the non-striker's end. It has been referred to third umpire but the batsman was home.
flighted outside off, hit down to long-off
leans forward to push to the off side
skids on to the middle and off line, defended on the front foot
loopy delivery just outside off, tries to paddle, misses and is struck on the pad outside the off stump
stays back to punch it to short extra cover
turns in slowly, Guptill stays back to punch it down to long-on
That's his fifty. He moves down the track and on drives to long-on. He raises his bat towards the dressing room where his team-mates give him a generous hand
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
couple of steps down the track and driven to short extra cover
advances down the track and brings up the 100 with a drive to long-off
flighted slowly on the off stump line, squeezed out to point
top-edges the sweep over the keeper for couple of runs
lands around the off stump line, driven to long-on
slows up the pace, tosses it outside off, driven to short extra cover
drifts down the leg side, rolls off the pad to short fine-leg region
full and well outside off, cut down to backward point
moves down the track, takes it on the full and drives to the off side of the pitch. Afridi gets his boot in the way but the ball ricochets to long-off
Clatter. Guptil sashayed down the track, reached the pitch of the flighted delivery and swung it high over long-on
flighted outside off, slower through the air, pushed to point
tossed up, turned to short midwicket
quicker one, short in length, punched to long-on
chips down the track and drives to Younis at short extra cover
quicker one, around the off stump line, squeezed out to backward point
legbreak on the off stump line, pushed carefully to the off side
advances down the track and lofts it towards long-off
long hop and it has been punished without any fuss. McCullum brings the 100 of the partnership with a pull to wide midwicket boundary
Fab slog sweep. He went down on his back knee and disposed the flighted delivery from almost outside off over midwicket boundary
And so, Afridi pushes this further outside off ,left alone
gets forward to defend and the camera pans to Vettori who has a lovely little smile
leans forward to push to the off side
Guptill goes down town. He charged down the track and lofted it cleanly to long-off boundary. Just one bounce and over the ropes. What's more that's his 6th ODI fifty
turns this one towards deep midwicket
outside off stump, pushed out to cover
quicker one, on the middle and leg, driven past the diving Ajmal to long-on
from round the stumps now, flighted delivery, Guptil comes down the track and eases it to long-on
turns away from the off stump, worked towards long-on
slider on the middle stump line, turned past square-leg
Flamboyant whack over long-on. He waltzed down the track, got to the pitch of the flighted delivery and lifted it cleanly high over long-on
reaches out well outside off stump and mistimes it to cover
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
moves forward to defend back down the track
drifts to the pads, shoveled past square-leg
again on the pads, clipped well to the left of Afridi at deep midwicket region
length delivery on the off stump, pushed past the non-striker for a single
slightly short in length, in the corridor, McCullum is beaten on the cut
length delivery around the middle and off line, punched past the bowler for a single

Guptill throws his wicket away. He walked down the track, looking for the big hit, Razzaq shortened the length and Guptill flat-batted his heave towards sweeper cover.. fine innings, though from Guptill
loud shout for lbw but turned down. It was the on the off stump line, drifting in and Taylor gets a inside edge to the pad
Afridi the rock star strikes. The slider does the trick. It was outside off stump, skidded on straight almost, Taylor pushed outside the line and stabbed it on to the stumps
on the off stump, turns away, pushed to the off side
flighted down the leg side .. wide
flighted legbreak outside off, padded away
full and well outside off, left alone
length delivery that straightens on the middle and off line, Styris shapes to work it across the line and gets a leading edge past point
short in length around off stump, defended to the off side
good delivery moves in late towards middle, almost hits the pad first but McCullum just about manages to stab it away
beaten outside off. It was the length delivery that moved away, Styris tried to drive it on the up through covers but ...
short in length around off, Styris goes for another on-the-up punchy drive and this time almost holes out to mid-off. It fell just short of the lunging fielder
on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
on the middle and off, styris pushes it rather tentatively down the track
spins away from the off stump, square driven to point
on the middle stump line, quicker, skids on, pushed out to the on side
just outside off stump, mistimes the cut to cover
tossed up, full outside off, driven to deep cover
on the middle stump line, eased down to long-on
on the middle stump line, pushed down to long-on
Bosh. It was the short of length delivery outside off and Styris slapped it way over mid-on
short in length outside off, punched to deep cover

Styris is run out Direct hit from Younis Khan. It was pushed past the diving short extra cover and McCullum calls Styris for a single. It was easy for McCullum as he was already down the track when he played that shot. Styris had to wait to see the short cover didn't stop it before he responded to the call. Too late. Younis, at mid-off,  swoops on the ball and fires down the stumps. Gone!
leans forward to punch to the off side
short in length, just outside off, pulled down to deep midwicket
stays back to clip it behind square-leg
goes down on his knee to swing it to deep backward square-leg
leans forward to wrist it to deep midwicket
flighted on the middle and off line, McCullum leans across to defend to cover
And again.
flighted outside off, goes for the sweep but misses
again tries to pull off the sweep shot but again, no contact. Ajmal had slowed up the pace further
really full delivery outside off, guided to short third man
around the off stump, steered again to short third man
he sure likes that sweep shot. Makes contacts this time to pick up a single
outside off stump, goes on straight, steered to backward point region
goes down on his back knee and unfurls a fierce sweep shot to pick up a boundary
stabbed to short fine-leg region
plays another sweep shot and will collect couple of runs
nice loopy delivery,  Vettori is beaten on the flight and edges it to short third man region
loud shout for lbw .. full delivery on the leg stump line, McCullum misses the sweep and is hit in front of leg. Hawk eye suggest it would have clipped leg stump
leans forward to defend
Another sweep. Another single
leans forward to drive through the off side for a single
slows up the pace but drops it short and Vettori latches on to it with crunchy pull to wide midwicket boundary
leans forward to turn it to deep midwicket
turns in from outside off, McCullum is rapped on the pad outside off stump
lovely inside-out off drive. It was floated outside off, full, McCullum crashed it well to the left of long-off

Ouch. Dan is hurt. Struck by the bouncer. It was the lifting delivery around the off and middle line, Vettori took his eyes off the ball as he tried to fend it away in an ungainly manner. The ball moved past the bat and hit him on the helmet ...
length delivery on the middle, pushed to the on side
full in length, outside off stump, angles away, McCullum is beaten on the drive
classy inside-out drive. It was the full delivery and McCullum creams it through extra cover
angling away from McCullum who pushes at it and gets a thick edge down to third man
turns in from outside off, hits the pad outside off stump
flighted outside off, driven to long-off
leans forward to edge the flick to his pad
flighted outside off stump, Vettori goes for the sweep, gets a bottom edge and the ball goes below Kamran's gloves and runs between his legs
gets forward to sweep it to midwicket
quicker, flatter, around off, defended on the front foot
fullish, around off stump, deflected to short midwicket
moves right across, exposes all the three stumps, and tries to glance a short-of-length delivery, misses and the ball bounces over the stumps to Kamran
just outside off, Vettori tries to dab it to third man but is beaten again
connects this time and gets a single down to third man
around the off stump line, squeezed to backward point
length delivery angling away from the off stump, McCullum tries to push it to covers but is beaten
just outside off, chopped down to third man
short in length, outside off stump, punched through extra cover
on the pads, clipped wide of Afridi at fine-leg region
short in length, punched past the bowler for a single
leans across to work a length delivery well to left of long-on for couple of runs
hangs on the back foot to work it past square-leg
banged in short outside off, Vettori waits before upper cutting it to wide third man region
moves right outside off to clip a length delivery from outside off to deep backward square-leg!
on the leg and middle, turned to short midwicket
back of length around middle and leg, swatted past square-leg
slower one, full in length, pushed out to cover
lot more fuller this time, Vettori shuffles across to work it to the on side
It was a length delivery on the middle and leg, flicked away to deep square-leg region
just outside off stump, whipped wide of mid-on
length delivery on the off stump line, pushed out to long-off
slightly short in length around the off stump, Vettori went for the pull but top-edged it up in the air and Kamran Akmal gets under it
full in length, slips in to beat the flick and strikes the pad. Shout for lbw but it was missing leg stump
leans across to punch on the up to deep point region
short in length, outside of stump, cut down to deep point
goes right back to punch it to Afridi
Dead plumb. Done in by the googly. It landed on a length around off stump and broke back in to move past the nervous waft  and hit him in front of middle.
another googly, squeezed out to point
moves right back to push it to long-off
just outside off stump, cut down hard to right of backward point where Shoaib Malik makes a super diving stop
in the zone outside off , slower one, left alone
full delivery, driven to yousuf at long-off
short in length, on the middle and off, bunted out to long-off . on 99 now. He has just one ODI hundred
back of length, worked to straightish midwicket, Oram thinks about a single before screaming NOOOO
fuller, again driven to midwicket
on the middle and leg, tapped past short midwicket
goes right back to shovel it to mid-off region . Baz on strike.
And that's his hundred. He celebrates in style. It was pushed to covers and off he dashed across .. He screams out a roar and punches in the air. Afridi congratulates him and so does Oram
leans forward to drive through the off side
quicker one, skids on to middle and leg line, jabbed to the on side
leans forward to fist it to long-on
googly, takes the edge and rushes past the lone slip
stays adjacent to the line of a short-of-a-length delivery and cuts it hard to sweeper cover
full in length, around the off stump, driven to long-off
full delivery, driven to long-off
around that off stump, chopped away to point region
swing and a miss. Length deliver in the corridor, McCullum tries to force it through the off side but makes no contact
short in length, around off, guided to backward point
on the off stump line, squeezed to square-leg
goes for the paddle scoop but doesn't make proper contact
low full toss on the leg and middle line, turned to midwicket for a single
charges out down the track and crashes a full delivery to deep cover boundary
Another big hit... walks down the track and square-drives it over cover
moves outside leg stump, goes for the big swing across the line but edges it behind square-leg
Almost a six over fine-leg! He moved outside off stump, crouched  and paddle scooped a low full toss on the middle to fine-leg
length delivery on the leg stump line, rolls off the pad
clears the front leg and swings to long-on
tries to repeat that paddle scoop again, misses and the ball moves past the off stump and Kamran doesn't collect it cleanly
backs away to force it through cover point
yorker length on the leg stump line, squeezed out to fine-leg
forces it well to the right of mid-on where Younis makes a fine diving stop
fires in a lovely yorker on the leg stump line, dug out to the on side
ha! Much fun. McCullum moved outside off and tried to repeat the paddle scoop. Gul fired in a yorker and it hit the bottom of the bat and rolled back to Gul who has a laugh
another yorker length delivery on the leg stump line, jabbed out to midwicket
moves outside leg and drives hard to mid-off. Younis picks up the ball and fires the throw. It misses the stumps and hits Oram's bat and he lets the bat slip out of his hand
moves outside leg, full toss outside off stump and Oram can't reach it
moves outside leg, has a big swing across the line but no wood on leather
reaches across to tap a single to point region
Wallop. It was the length delivery on the leg stump line, McCulum short-arm pulls it over backward square-leg boundary. Superb piece of timing
clears the front leg and mistimes the pull through midwicket. he runs really hard to come back for the second run
chest-high full toss outside off  - it has to be a no ball and it is - McCullum goes for the pull and top edges it over Kamran
short of length delivery, bounces past the attempted slog and Kamran collects
moves outside leg and drags his slog to deep backward square-leg
Baz's super innings comes to an end. He cleared the front leg and went for the good-old slog to the on side but dragged it off the inner edge from well outside off to his stumps.
in the zone outside off, moves past the intended big drive to Kamran
banged in short, jabbed over point
moves outside leg and pushes the full delivery to left of mid-off
Gul keeps firing in those yorkers. Awesome stuff. This one is on the middle, just about dug out to the off side
turns in from outside off, clipped through midwicket
outside off, goes past the sweep shot
on the off stump line, steered to cover point
doosra but well outside off .. wide
Kamran shouts for a catch behind decision. It was another doosra, Mills took couple of steps down the track, had a big swing across the line, missed and dragged his back foot in the crease
charges down the track, reaches the pitch of the delivery and smokes it over the straight boundary
moves outside leg, goes for the big lofted drive but drags it straight to long-on
Oram now goes outside leg stump, tries to ping wide midwicket boundary but makes no contact. The ball whooshes past the leg stump
really full delivery, driven past Gul for a single; they think about the second but decide against it
Flashed away! It was a length delivery outside off and Bond carved it to backward point boundary
length delivery again, pushed out through covers
low full toss on the leg stump line, bunted out wide of long-on for couple of runs
skips down the track and miscues the lofted hit towards deep midwicket. Salman Butt rushes in but misjudges it completely and lunges out in the end but can;t' get a hand to it
comes forward to mow it past the bowler and they scamper back for the second run. 300 up for NZ
reaches out to fetch it from well outside off and hit it down to long-on

Another catch goes down. Butt again. It was miscued towards deep midwicket. Younis ran back, Butt ran in but since it was closer to Butt Younis stopped. But Butt didn't move in quickly enough. Younis now goes to deep midwicket and sends Butt inside the circle
goes down the track but doesn't connect properly and gets back to his crease
doosra outisde off stump, Bond went for the big swing down town but missed it completely. Akmal breaks the stumps, appeals for stumping and the third umpire says not out.

inn2.comm: leans forward to defend a length delivery to the on side
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
lifting delivery outside off stump, Butt drops his wrists and lets the ball go through to McCullum
leans forward to push a length delivery to cover
short in length, well outside the off stump, Butt reaches out, tries to cut but gets a bottom edge and the ball rolls to Baz
full in length, around the off stump, leans forward to defend
short in length, cuts in to the middle and leg, Latif clips it past square-leg
cuts in from the middle stump to rap him on the pad
short of length, extra bounce outside off, Latif wafts under the ball
short in length, moves in towards off and middle, pushed out to bowler
full in length, around off stump line, stabbed back down the track
leans forward to drive to right of mid-off where Southee makes a fine diving stop
lands outside leg stump and goes down even further. Wide
short in length, straightens outside off stump, defended to cover
cuts in to the middle and leg line, clipped to deep square-leg and Bond gets across to stop it
short in length and outside off stump, Butt plays a superb wristy cut shot
from round the stumps, very full delivery, squeezed out to backward point
cuts in towards the middle, turned to square-leg
full in length, driven sweetly but straight to mid-off
full delivery outside off  stump, dug out to cover
short and wide, cut hard but straight to cover where Guptill stops
fires across a bouncer, It gets big on Latif who pulls it behind square-leg
around 137 kmph full in length, on the middle stump line, pushed out to mid-off
banged in short, in the corridor, left alone
length delivery straightening on the middle stump, defended back down the pitch
on the middle and off line ,cutting in, turned to midwicket
a bouncer and Latif ducks
full in length, on the middle, pushed to Vettori at mid-on
banged in short around the off stump line, left alone
superb shot. It was a length delivery just outside off stump and Latif punched it on the up and through extra cover
really full delivery around off, driven to mid-off
fullish again, driven straight to cover
lands on a length around leg stump line, moves to the off stump line, defended to the off side
the bouncer outside off stump, Butt goes for the pull but doesn't connect
short delivery again, doesn't climb all that high and Butt pulls it through midwicket
in the zone outside off stump, Butt is beaten, trying to run it down to third man
bouncing leg cutter on the off and middle line, tapped to the on side
on the middle and leg, turned to left of short fine-leg and Bond stops and has a shy at the striker's end but Latif gets back in time
full in length, on the middle stump line, tapped to the on side
short in length, around off stump line, guided to backward point
pushes this wide down the leg side
slower one, again drifting down leg side and Latif flicks it past short fine-leg fielder
short in length, well outside off, cut down to wide third man
full delivery outside off, steered to third man
shout for lbw. It cut in from outside off, from round the stumps, and rapped him on the pad. struck just outside off stump
short in length, dragged to mid-on
just outside off stump, bouncing from back of length, pushed out to point
overpitched outside off stump and Butt drives it through covers
length delivery on the off stump line, pushed to cover.
on the off stump, again punched out to cover
bounces just outside off, Latif stays adjacent to the line and punches it wide of third man
short and wide, again cut down to the right of third man

another boundary from the last ball of the over. It was a length delivery just outside off, Butt opens the bat-face and tries to run it to third man, gets an edge and the ball runs lot finer, through the vacant slip region
slower one , outside off stump, swung away to right of mid-on
lovely cover drive. It was the low full toss and Latif caresses it through covers
full again, goes under the bat and rushes to McCullum
around the off stump, guided to third man
from round the stumps now, yorker length outside off, dug out to point
low full toss outside off, steered through point.
full delivery, rolls off the pad to short fine-leg
around the off stump line, defended to off side
on the middle and off stump line, flicked past square-leg
bouncer on the middle stump line and Latif goes down under
fires in another short delivery and Latif ducks again
short in length, slightly slower one outside off stump and Latif times it superbly past point. He wristed that on the up
leans well forward to defend to cover
leans well forward to push to cover and they rush across for the quick single.
full in length, just outside off stump, pushed to left of mid-off
leans forward to defend the slower one
cuts in towards off stump, pushes it to cover point, wants a single but Latif sends him back. Taylor rushes across from short cover
gets forward to defend another length delivery from round the stumps
leans forward to push it away to the off side
beaten outside off. Southee, from round the stumps, pitches it on a length outside off and gets it to skid past the outside edge
around the off stump, punched to sweeper cover

almost a mix-up. It was pushed to mid-off and they set for a single before changing their mind. Vettori flicks it to non-striker;s end but that's the wrong end. Butt was already in, it was Latif who had gone half-way down the track
banged in short, swatted over to deep backward square-leg region where Styris makes a diving stop
just outside off stump, run down to third man
full in length, outside off stump, slower one, pushed to point
length delivery just outside off stump, pushed out to cover
leans well forward to defend a slower one
just outside off stump, yet another slower one, pushed out to cover
just outside off stump, run down to third man
on the middle stump line, flicked past square-leg
drifts to the pads and Latif glances it well to the right of short fine-leg fielder
slower one, outside off, punched away to backward point
on a length around the off stump, punched to deep cover
from round the stumps, length delivery on the middle and off, defended down the track
slower one, well outside off stump, hit down to Styris at sweeper cover
on a length, around off stump, pushed to cover point for a single
slower one, full and outside off, Latif scoops it over mid-off and it runs away to the boundary.

leans across to sweep from well outside off stump

outside off stump, steered past point

shout for lbw .. flighted delivery on the middle and off, Younis goes for the sweep, misses and it strikes the pad ... Close. Very close. It was hitting leg stump, says Hawk eye. The ball hit the bat after hitting the pad and almost rolled back to the off stump!
leans forward to push it away for a single
flighted delivery outside off, driven to cover
works this one through midwicket for a single
length delivery from round the stumps, defended to cover
full in length outside off stump, edges the drive to the off side
short in length, outside off stump, Younis is beaten on the cut shot

Almost a run out. Around the off stump line, pushed to the off side and they set off for the quick single. Broom rushes in from backward point and underarms the throw over the stumps. Had he hit. Butt would have been run out
short in length and outside off stump, cut away past point
short in length, just outside off stump, steered to third man
flighted on the leg and middle line, rolls off the pad t
fuller, outside off stump, driven to sweeper cover
on the middle and off line, driven to long-on
slows up the pace, tosses it on a length, Younis stretches forward to mistime the drive to cover
shout for lbw but it was probably missing leg stump..
flighted on the off stump, Butt brings up his 12th ODI fifty with a sweep shot. He looks up the skies and says a prayer
length delivery skidding down leg, rolls off the pad
moves outside leg stump and powers it to sweeper cover
leans forward to flick it to deep midwicket
just outside the off stump, chopped down to third man
fullish around off stump, driven to mid-off
full in length, driven straight to short extra cover
quicker one, short in length, pulled to deep midwicket
flatter, quickish again, swung away to deep midwicket region.

flighted on the middle and off, Younis pushes it out to the off side
slows up the pace, tossed outside off , Younis edges the sweep to short fine-leg
full and on the middle, Younis pushes it towards backward point, wants a single but is sent back in time
bounces from short of length, pulled away to deep midwicket

What a stunner from Ross Taylor! It was a fullish delivery on the leg and middle, Younis flicked it away to the right of short midwicket where Taylor moves to his right before diving with the outstretched right hand and plucks the catch.
high bouncer .. harmless and wide

That man Taylor again. It was the back of length delivery, clipped away in the air over short midwicket and Taylor jumps up to grab it. Scott Styris and Rossy didn't do much with the bat but they are combining here superbly for NZ
leans forward to push it away for a single
short in the length, on the off stump, stabbed off the inner edge
short in length outside off stump, punched away to deep point
leans forward to defend
flighted delivery on the middle and off, pushed out to the bowler
on the middle stump line, pushed out to the off side
short in length, skids on just outside off stump, cut away to the point region
shout for lbw ... on the off and middle stump line, Butt is hit on the pad, trying to sweep but it was probably going on to miss off. Hawk eye says it would have hit off
leans forward to clip it past square-leg
charges out, moves down the leg side and drives to sweeper cover
hurls across a bouncer and Akmal shapes to pull but withdraws from the shot as the ball climbs more than he anticpated
full in length, driven to right of long-on
length delivery on the middle and off, pushed out to the off side
Scott Styris is having a night of his life. It was a length delivery outside off and Akmal punches straight to short cover. Advantage New Zealand.
on the middle stump line, turned past square-leg
leans forward to push it to short extra cover
skips down the track and pushes it to left of midwicket

Butt is run out. It was pushed to the left of midwicket and there is confusion between the two. Guptil makes a superb diving stop and quickly flicks the ball to Vettori with Butt nowhere in picture. Yousuf called Butt for the single before he changed his mind. Too late.
flighted outside off, driven to right of short extra cover where another diving stop is made
spins away from the off stump, Yousuf goes back to late cut it wide of backward point
leans forward to push it away for a single
fullish, on the legs, rolls away of the pad
just outside off stump, chopped down to third man
Monster hit. Yousuf charges down the track and lifts the length delivery over long-on. Awesome hit.
in the zone outside off stump, moves past the attempted dab to third man and goes to the keeper
shout for lbw ... It was the full length delivery on the middle and leg and Yousuf is hit high on the pad/. Hawk eye says it would have hit the top of the leg stump
goes for the big sweep but doesn't connect well
quicker one, flatter trajectory, arm- ball, punched through point
leans forward to defend and edges it to short fine-leg fielder
full on the middle, wristed through midwicket
moves down the track and drives down to long-on
around the off stump line, defended to backward point
full in length on the middle and leg, tries to work it across the line, gets a leading edge to the off side
moves down the track and mistimes the cut to left of cover. Guptill has a shy at the non-striker's end and gives away an extra run
moves outside leg, Styris follows him, jabbed out to the on side

dropped by McCullum down the leg side. Malik threatened to move down leg side before he shuffled to the off. Styris kept it on the middle and Malik glanced it down the leg side. McCullum lunged to his left but couldn't scoop it up
leans forward to drive through the on side
leans forward to on drive it wide of long-on
arm-ball around off, mistimes his drive to cover, Malik wants a single but Yousuf, wisely, sends him back
goes down the track and drives to long-on
Super arm-ball does the trick. Trapped in front. It curved in from outside off, to hit the front pad first before it hit the bat. "Pad first and that's out, " says Geoff Boycott on air.

Huge huge shout for lbw. How close was that? How didn't he give that out? It was plumb. It was the arm-ball, moved past the waft and struck him on the back pad in front of middle stump but the umpire Zameer Haider turns it down. Perhaps he thought there was some insideedge there. Oh dear.
just outside off, stabbed to point
short in length, outside off, pushed away to backward point
the sharp bouncer and a surprised Razzaq fends it off in the air but it drops well short of point
bouncing outside off stump, punched to backward point
another lifting delivery outside off, Razzaq sways away
another short delivery, climbs outside off, Razzaq is late on the pull and McCullum collects it
short in length, bouncing in towards middle stump, defended to the off side.
the bouncer on the middle stump line and Malik ducks
banged in short again and Malik unfurls a forehand cross court to ping wide midwicket boundary. Flat-batted slap!
fuller, outside off stump, reaches out to drive to left of short cover where Guptil makes a tumbling stop
leans forward to punch to long-off
the bouncer on the middle stump line, pulled down to deep midwicket
Lovely shot from Malik. He moved forward and lifted it cleanly over mid-off. Nice swing of the bat.
banged in short again, pulled to deep midwicket
lovely bouncing slower delivery that straightens outside off; it goes past the edge and it bounces just before McCullum who makes a mess of it
fires a bouncer, ducks
short in length, outside off stump, punched away to short cover
kicks up from short of length, pushed to mid-off for a single
full in length, on the middle stump line, defended to the off side of the pitch
banged in short around off stump, sways away. Lot of short boundaries in these last few overs. They were guilty of bowling it full in the last game.
moves outside leg to punch it in the air and it goes to long-off
banged in short again, this time on the leg stump line, pulled to long leg
pushes it down the leg side, Malik was looking to go down the leg side and Mills tried to follow him
shuffles across, hops to tuck the bouncing short delivery past square-leg
moves outside leg and swings it to deep square-leg
moves outside leg stump, Mills bowls another short-pitched delivery that climbs over off stump line, Malik reaches out to upper cut it over point
Thwack. Razzaq backs away from the stumps and swing a full delivery to wide long-on boundary. Will the next one be the short delivery?
It is the short delivery and Razzaq mistimes the pull but clears midwicket
Another chest-high short delivery ,pulled away to deep midwicket
lovely shot. It was the slow bouncer, around 113 kmph, Malik moved outside leg, waited and deliberately carved it over short third man fielder ...
full delivery this time, driven to long-off
fullish outside off, driven to deep cover
full delivery on the middle and leg, dragged down to deep square-leg region
The fielding has been terrific. Southee, now, takes a very sharp catch. It was drilled  low to his left at extra cover where he lunges to take a smart catch
pushed to the off side for a single
moves outside leg, has a big slog across the line and edges it over the vacant slip region
short in length, swung away to deep midwicket
short in length, clipped past square-leg
full delivery outside off stump, edges the drive to the ground and it bounces away to McCullum
moves down the leg side ... Wide
bangs it in short, Gul is late on the pull shot
another one down the leg side and McCullum dives to his left but couldn't stop it completely
the short lifting delivery, Razzaq bunts it down to long-on
short in length, outside off, Gul has a wild swing and a miss. Southee appeals for a catch, McCullum, who collected the ball, doesn't appeal
fires across a bouncer and Gul sways away
yet another wide down the leg side
short delivery outside off, chopped away to third man
on a length, on the middle, defended to the off side
swing and a miss. It rushes past the off stump to McCullum

The short-stuff has worked today. Gul steers the bouncing delivery outside off to backward point.
full delivery outside off stump, square driven to deep point region
short in length, bouncing away past the attempted cut shot to Baz
And again.
bouncer, face-high, and Aamer does well to sway away from it
back to the chest-high bouncing delivery and again, Aamer is beaten
short in length outside off, punched away to backward point
Thunderous hit. It was the short delivery and Razzaq was expecting it  - Mills doesn't have the pace as well, and smashed it over midwicket boundary
oh lovely delivery but Razzaq gets the edge to fine-leg boundary. It was the slow yorker, Razzaq picked it up very late, tried to jam his bat down and got the edge
backs away outside leg and swings it past square-leg
full in length outside off, mistimes it towards cover
The beamer and Mills says sorry and walks to Razzaq who accepts the apology and shakes hand .. It was the full toss that went towards the face of Razzaq who manages to get down just in time
around 121 kmph yorker, dug out to square-leg .. Mills offers another apology to Razzaq.
short in length outside off, punched away to deep cover
full in length, Aamer seems to have been expecting a short delivery as he was looking to back away before he came in line to push the ball to the off side
the short delivery arrives this time, upper cut towards third man.. catch it was the cry from Bond but it falls just short
yorker length outside off stump, Razzaq tries to squeeze it out through point but can't get bat to ball
length delivery outside off stump, square driven to deep point
Cracking shot from Aamer. It was the short delivery well outside off and Aamer lashed out at the width, cutting it over point
the slow yorker on the middle, squeezed out to backward point
Moves outside the leg stump, gives himself some room and goes for the big lofted shot down the ground but holes out to long-off
bounced in short, allowed to go through to the keeper
fullish delivery, lofted to right of mid-off where Vettori dives for the catch but couldn't reach it
Aamer provides more ammunition to suggest he should bat higher than Gul. It was the short delivery outside off, he cut it over point
fullish, on the stumps, edged to midwicket
stands tall to punch it to covers
All over. Full and outside off stump, square driven to deep point . New Zealand players shake hands with each other and with the Pakistani players. The series stands 1 -1. Exciting finale awaits us.
